  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is correct. It&rsquo;s given that the total mass, in kilograms, of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> identical objects is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\"><mi>t</mi></math>. To obtain the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146 r\"><mn>146</mn><mi>r</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> is multiplied by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146\"><mn>146</mn></math>. Therefore, to find the total mass, in kilograms, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146 r\"><mn>146</mn><mi>r</mi></math> of these objects, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\"><mi>t</mi></math> must also be multiplied by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146\"><mn>146</mn></math>. The result of multiplying&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\"><mi>t</mi></math> by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146\"><mn>146</mn></math> is the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146 t\"><mn>146</mn><mi>t</mi></math>. Therefore, the total mass, in kilograms, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146 r\"><mn>146</mn><mi>r</mi></math> of these objects, is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"146 t\"><mn>146</mn><mi>t</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>",
